description:
4 projects made by me (starting programming all by myself, using online e-books, videos and other stuff).
 They're all finished and published in their folder. For some reason Visual Studio (2012 Ultimate) won't allow me to publish them &quot;to a file path&quot;, so I had to publish them as for CDs (with installer).
The projects have the code commented by me, also, for starting users to understand what's going on there. 
Projects are:
1) &quot;Age- Cases&quot;
Consists on showing what Cases (a type of conditionals) do in a very simple project which asks the user to put in a number and then shows a MessageBox with text.

2) &quot;Conditionals&quot;
Shows how &quot;If... Then... Else... End If&quot; sentences work by asking the user to write a number between 10 and 20.

3) &quot;For Loop&quot;
Shows how the For Loop works.

4) &quot;Multipliers -For Loop&quot;
This one shows how the &quot;For Loop&quot; works showing that it can also multiply. In this one the user is asked to put a StarterNumber, an EnderNumber and a Multiplier, then shows in the ListBox the result for each multiplication.

Well, that was all. If you like this comment it here and I'll add more as I learn. I hope you'll pardon me if you see any grammar mistake, I'm not a natural english speaker, even though I go to classes.
